All US spending on the War in Afghanistan exceeded $2 trillion.

Since February 24, 2022, countries and international organizations have allocated more than $150,8 billion to help Ukraine.

And all the life extension startups in the world are raising around $2 billion in cumulative investment per year.

Elon Musk has calculated that it would take $1 trillion to successfully colonize Mars. Just the money that the US spent on the War in Afghanistan would be enough for this.


Recently, there have been successes in rejuvenation of the body. If more money were allocated to the fight against aging, then success could be achieved faster.

For example, scientists have managed to reverse aging in mice. Researchers now face the challenge of replicating this in humans. Harvard Medical School biologist David Sinclair has learned how to rejuvenate laboratory rodents. It is reported that with the help of proteins, scientists were able to turn old cells into stem cells, and also returned them to earlier versions. Tested mice with poor eyesight "updated" it and began to see almost "better than their offspring." Scientists thus managed to restore vision to old mice, while they are sure that in the same way it is possible to literally “reset age” and update other body systems, including humans. "We think it could be a universal process that can be applied to the entire body to 'reset our' age," said David Sinclair. Research into the genetic intervention that helped mice rejuvenate is still in its early stages, he said, and it will take years for human trials to be completed.

The famous Harvard geneticist George Church predicted the defeat of aging within 10 years.

Anti-aging enthusiasts such as British gerontologist Aubrey de Gray and Mikhail Batin, head of the Russian Science for Life Extension Foundation, complain about the lack of funding. Progress in this area, in their opinion, could go much faster.

According to the British gerontologist Aubrey de Gray, the main problem is the lack of money for research: “We are working on a cure, we have some progress, but everything is moving very slowly. First of all, because we don't have enough people. We are already proving that this product will eventually work."


Instead of funding the fight against aging and the colonization of other planets, the leadership of countries finances wars. As a result, scientific and technological progress slows down. Over the moment, an oligarchy has developed in the United States, which is one of the forms of autocracy. Scholars Martin Gilens of Princeton and Benjamin Page of Northwestern University conducted a study that showed that the policies of the United States government are in the interests of the rich and their influence groups, and not the wishes of the majority. The scientists note that “the main conclusion that follows from our study is that economic elites and organized groups representing the interests of business have the ability to significantly influence the policies pursued by the US government, while groups formed to protect the interests of the masses, and ordinary citizens have little to no influence.

The real income of the average American has not risen for several decades, despite the fact that GDP per capita has been growing during this time. The oligarchs benefited from this growth, while the Americans got nothing. In 2011, according to PolitiFact and others, the top 400 richest Americans "have more wealth than half of all Americans combined." The US has a high Gini coefficient.

Although the United States is the largest economy in the world, it still does not have free medicine and higher education. More than 20% of American adults have difficulty writing, and some can't even read a newspaper, ABC reported. This was shown by a study of the International Program for the Assessment of Adult Competence (PIAAC) under the auspices of the US Department of Education. According to the study, one in five adults in the US has a very low literacy rate. 43.5 million Americans experience difficulties with writing and reading. And we are talking not only about migrants, but about people who speak English from birth. “The historical and political illiteracy of the population is quite high in North America. Comment: My earliest childhood memory is looking up at the face of an iron lung.  I got polio in 1953 at the age of three and was completely paralyzed from the neck down for the first 6 months and spent that time in the machine.  Eventually the paralysis went away in my left side, and it developed normally, but my right side, including my lung, never fully developed.  Spent most of my youth in wheelchairs or on crutches and having surgery after surgery, having spent cumulatively 6 years in hospitals before my 18th birthday.  My right leg was 3.5 inches (9cm) shorter than my left and when I was ten years old I had an experimental surgery where 16 huge metal staples were put into the growth centers of my left knee to stop the leg from growing for two years until it caught up, and then they were removed.  I like to tell people that "I'm taller than I really am," as I'm 5'9-1/2" (176.5cm) tall when I really should be 6'1" (185.4cm).  Through my childhood polio was a challenge and most of this time was before hospitals had televisions in the rooms or wards, so I read almost every book in the library at Gillette State Hospital for Crippled Children in St. Paul, MinneSNOWta including the dictionary and the full Encyclopedia Britannica.  After some college I went to work in the transportation industry, working my way up until I was a consultant and transportation software developer and on to the Director of Transportation of 35 divisions of one of the largest companies on the planet.  I couldn't play stick and ball sports, and as I grew up in my father's service station I raced snowmobiles, motorcycles and cars and spent much of my life with anything mechanical.  I've acted in many national, regional and local radio and television commercials,  I've been in a couple of movies and am a published author.  I've traveled extensively through 45 states, Canada and Mexico, done a 10-day solo, canoeing and portaging in the Boundary Waters Canoe Area on the Minnesota/Ontario border.  Likewise, I've been around computers since the 1960s and sent my first e-mail on ARPANET back in the early 1970s, ran national BBSes in the 80s and started my Website design company in 1994.  And I've done so much more of note than could be listed here.  Polio pushed me to excel at almost everything I did, and gave me the empathy to for many years establish programs to help other physically challenged children.  I'm now 74 years old, my life is winding down, and sometimes regret my childhood, but never regret what it has helped me to accomplish.

Comment:
I could write a book on my gambling over a 14 year period but its 2 much to put in this message...The moment I really needed help was the night before Xmas and I had spent all my money  I had nothing and  my Son had just been born...... I was going to end it all my wife had had enough.

My gambling started when I lost my home and the government made it legal to gamble online which has now got out of hand
 
117 to 496 gambling related suicides a year in England “associated with problem gambling or gambling disorder” which was produced by OHID and published in January 2023.

I picked up a phone and rang a helpline .I got 1 on 1 support over a 6month period  with really helped me and the support I needed..........I had tried to stop for 4 years prior...... 5 years later I am free gambling

My wife stood by me and I am very lucky.

I have gone back to university to do music and won a international music award and putting my compulsive  energy into something proactive which has changed my life. 

That year was the hardest time in my life trying to stop, I still get the the compulsive inner voice talking to me at times but I just shake it off

..........Things people can do.......... I hope this helps...............

When you get a serious issues you must seek help go see a doctor,  gambler local meet or help line

Put everything in place so you cant gamble such as going on Gamstop which is a UK service

Remember

Comment:
Consider a beautiful young waitress who works at a high end restaurant or a big casino or something like that. She makes between 150-300$ in tips everyday plus her salary. Pretty good money for someone who just completed high school and works only 40 hrs a week! One day, a rich old man offers her 2000$ to spend a night with him. At first she’s reluctant but considering the big amount, she agrees. Unfortunately, the manager finds out and she’s fired for sleeping with a customer for money. To make things worse, her boyfriend of 5+ years whom she wanted to marry finds out and breaks up with her. Now, she lost her job which paid her an average of 200$ a day and her future life partner. Was this worth it? A short term profit is never worth a long term loss. 
Gambling is just the same. People win here and there but in the long run, they always lose. Now, speaking of the million dollar life-changing progressive jackpots. Have you seen the odds of winning? They are somewhat around one in 20-80 million. Imagine, there are 50 million people and one of them stole your wallet which had 500$. Are you seriously going to search for your wallet? Comment: Growing and restoring forests is a much better solution for removing CO2 from the atmosphere than using Direct Carbon Removal Factories because the CO2 removed from the air by trees can be converted to breathable oxygen and the carbon can be used to replenish soil if not stored in trees instead of being buried in the ground as rocky waste with no use for humans and the environment.  Since much of the carbon and oxygen atoms in our atmosphere are locked in CO2 molecules, direct air removal technology impacts the atmosphere in a negative way by removing oxygen and carbon from the air changing the atmospheric composition by causing the atmospheric oxygen levels to decrease instead of recycling the CO2 into carbon and oxygen like it naturally should. In addition, direct air removal plants will increase deforestation because trees will lose their importance for carbon removal and people will have less of a reason to protect trees for the purpose of combating climate change. The only solution to reducing CO2 levels in the atmosphere without causing any of these negative externalities is to increase the number of trees and use of renewable energy sources such as wind and solar and decrease the use of greenhouse gas-producing sources such as fossil fuels.

Comment:
Thank goodness for all the members of the Queen's household.  Elizabeth II's death should remind us why monarchy is helpful.  Monarchy shouldn't be used as real-life soap opera, nor just as material to fill space in the media.

The achievement of the British monarchy should become clear in comparison with the histories of other countries.  In the 19th & 20th centuries the U.S.A, France, Germany, Russia, Italy, Spain and Greece suffered in various ways civil wars, political storms, and dictatorships.  This shows what can go wrong in the absence of a head of state which is above politics, and which opposes illegal dictatorship.  If there are many reasons England, Wales, and Scotland have had no civil war since Culloden in 1746, having a constitutional monarchy to unify all the people is an important reason.  In the UK, 'peace' in formal speech is "The King's Peace".

Of course King Charles III's first marriage was a tragic mistake; Prince Philip could be tactless; he & Elizabeth II made mistakes as parents.  Whatever mistakes the royal family have made, let us be grateful for the unity the monarchy gives the UK & the world.  By stabilizing Britain & the commonwealth (e.g. Canada & Australia), it promotes peace in the world.  The sea around it didn't protect the U.S.A. against civil war in the 1860s, and the UK could have suffered civil war over slavery in the 19th century; likewise over world war, loss of empire, economic failure, or race in the 20th.  There will always be violence and political problems in the world, and billions of people who know or understand nothing of the British monarchy and the stability it brings.  Since the 1700s, billions of people have lived under the British crown without civil war, lynching, dictatorship in their lives.  God save King Charles III, and his successors.

Comment:
I figured out I had undiagnosed adhd in my 20’s, I also suffered years of post partum mood disorders while having and raising my children. I more or less for by with my own coping mechanisms whether they were healthy or not. I finally sought out a diagnosis at 44 to be able to try medication because I was burned out and becoming unable to work, and spiraling. I’m glad I wasn’t dismissed as “depressed” or just perimenopausal and my NP took me seriously. 
My head is definitely noisy! 😅 I was a day dreamer as a child, and books were a refuge. I could hyperfocus on something for hours. I have dyscalculia which added to the school days  math class struggles. All this really added up to deep struggle with self esteem, something I still wrestle with. I am too hard on myself much of the time!

Comment: Men can be just as likely to experience it.  I am diagnosed with the non hyperactive one.  That doesn't mean that I don't "stim" some.   I fidget with things a lot.  I am not the stereotypical ADHD type rocking back and forth.  I also had a horrible time with some subjects in school like math.  In reading I was known to follow the book with my finger.  It is all in papers my attorney filed and gave me copies of.  I strongly recommend a cheap document feeder.  I got one used from eBay and had them all scanned to my computer by a close personal friend.  I had it done on my computer so that there would not be copies unknown to me on other peoples' computers.  My mother also used to fear that I might be more easily taken advantage of financially.  You know how mothers are, they worry and just want the best.  I mostly had them scanned since I would not know how to replace them if something ever happened to them.  Maybe my attorney still has them but I know getting that stuff from the SSA directly is a convoluted and unnecessarily complicated process.  On the form they give you they tell you they will not honor a request for just the whole folder but you have to be specific on what you want.  I don't know if they are just secretive or just lazy.  Maybe some people have a really large file and it would be too much to copy or digitize.  Maybe it is just a huge pain for them to do and they prefer you didn't ask.  I really don't know why.

Comment:
My brother, who was a few years older, was diagnosed ADHD in middle school. I, however, was great in school, so no one ever figured I had it, despite so many signs that might be noticed now. I've only just been diagnosed this year at the cusp of 40 with both ADHD and Autism, which rather blows my mind...
   I just always *knew* (& saw & experienced)I was different, and was told by my Mum over and over that I didn't think the way that other people did - this was neither a put-down, nor a compliment for being "special" - she was honest and got through to me. 
   So many of my behaviors make sense now that I always wondered about before.    
  However, I shirk no responsibility in shouldering the consequences of my actions in life by placing the blame on anything but my own choices/actions as well. What I mean to say is that I try not to use ADHD as an excuse, and learn how better to use it to my advantage.

Comment:
I am male and got diagnosed when i turned 35. 
My diognosis came from cambridge University at addenbrookes hospital over a 6 month period. 
Misdiagnosed by doctors through the years, given medication that i should not have been given. 
Its a difficult condition to have not only for you but for colleagues immediate family and anybody in-between. 
I have a very respected and responsible career that i have worked tirelessly over the last 18 years to establish and tomorrow i am in a meeting with group HR for resonable adjustments to help me have a competitive edge within my chosen career. 
ADHD certainly with my 48 years experience is a very lonely condition often being ostracised for being differnet, bullied in the workplace,  financial impacts, relationship turmoil the list is quite endless. 
Its ok not to be ok and i wish everyone of my fellow brothers and sisters of the adhd community every success in the future. 
Should anybody need any advice then please drop a comment here and i will try to offer you avenues you could explore, 

Stay safe folks and have a fantastic Christmas and New year

I was diagnosed with severe ADHD- Hyperactivity type when I was a young teenager… I had already been having obvious problems- been seeing a psychologist and an adolescent medicine doctor but what finally led to a formal psychiatrist and test was, was me almost dying of alcohol poisoning as a young teenager…. After that my parents fired the psychologist took me to the psychiatrist etc….. but that’s what I mean something that brings you to your knees, I have also been brought to my knees quite a few times since then too. That’s what I mean how did they get this far in life without something like that forcing them to get help?? What has them get help is watching a video on social media… so tell me how all of these thousands of women being diagnosed in the same time frame is not in some way a social contagion rather than women actually struggling with adhd- type inattentive?? AND most of all of the people being diagnosed now are not being thoroughly tested!

Comment:
I'm a 23yr old woman and my GP refused to refer me/couldn't get anywhere with the NHS so I went to a private specialist clinic that researches ADHD earlier this year, which is where I got my diagnosis.
However I've had to return to NHS to ask for treatment but cuz my diagnosis was made privately/not made by the NHS I've been waitlisted to be potentially diagnosed a second time.
Something really needs to be done to scrap the stereotype, as it costed me a lot of gaslighting and people refusing to fill out forms when I was taking my assessment with the private clinic, "You can't have ADHD cuz you're lazy, you're moody and when it comes to sleep you take ages in bed" is what people told me. Even I didn't recognise I had the disorder, I believed I was a normal person who was just never good enough.
The subject of me potentially having ADHD first came up when I was in secondary school, me and my school friends laughed cuz we thought it was a load of rubbish cuz I don't fit the stereotype.
Second time was when my mum found an article about how it affects women, she wanted me to read it. I kept putting it off cuz I wasn't interested but when I did she asked me what I thought about the symptoms---to which I said "There weren't any symptoms in that article" and she answered back with "Yes there were, and it's as if this article is describing you", I got mad and shouted "No mum, I don't have ADHD!!" at her (Well those words of mine aged like fine wine 😂)
After describing myself to friends and strangers and them telling me "Sounds like you have ADHD" was when I finally started to think "Okay, maybe I do have ADHD" and sought assessment

Comment:
I'm 36 and I mostly have ADD. 
I really struggled to pay attention to the teachers in school. When they were giving instructions to the class, my mind would wander, and when I finally snapped back; everyone would be working and I wouldn't have a clue what to do. It usually ended with me not having produced any work and the teacher pulling me to the front of the class to scream at me. To say this situation was stressful was an understatement. Everytime the teacher started giving instructions, I would be internally screaming at myself to stay focused. Listen to what they're saying. I would be panicking like crazy. But, it just seemed completely out of my control and my mind would inevitably wander. I hated it. Because I was shouted at every single time, my classmates started bullying me as well. I always felt like something was wrong with me. Led me to have a very deep depression and self hatred. Having a diagnosis finally allowed me to overcome depression, after suffering for years.

Would just like to add, that as an adult my ADD symptoms are practically non-existent. Definitely not completely gone, but I'm more than capable of staying focused to instructions now. But, the treatment I received as a kid, carried with me into adulthood, and I hated myself regardless of the improvement. It's crazy how such mistreatment as a child, can severely affect your adult life.

Comment:
BUDDHA

        Thus have I heard. On one occasion the Blessed One was living at Vesali in the grove outside the city to the west.
         Now on that occasion Sunakkhatta, son of the Licchavis, had recently left this Dhamma and Discipline.[1] He was making this statement before the Vesali assembly: "The recluse Gotama does not have any superhuman states, any distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones.[2] The recluse Gotama teaches a Dhamma (merely) hammered out by reasoning, following his own line of inquiry as it occurs to him, and when he teaches the Dhamma to anyone, it leads him when he practices it to the complete destruction of suffering."[3]
          Then, when it was morning, the Venerable Sariputta dressed, and taking his bowl and outer robe, went into Vesali for alms. Then he heard Sunakkhatta, son of the Licchavis, making this statement before the Vesali assembly. When he had wandered for alms in Vesali and had returned from his almsround, after his meal he went to the Blessed One, and after paying homage to him, he sat down at one side and told the Blessed One what Sunakkhatta was saying.
           The Blessed One said: "Sariputta, the misguided man Sunakkhatta is angry, and his words are spoken out of anger. Thinking to discredit the Tathagata, he actually praises him; [69] for it is a praise of the Tathagata to say of him: 'When he teaches the Dhamma to anyone, it leads him when he practices it to the complete destruction of suffering.'
             "Sariputta, this misguided man Sunakkhatta will never infer of me according to Dhamma: 'That Blessed One is accomplished, fully enlightened, perfect in true knowledge and conduct, sublime, knower of worlds, incomparable leader of persons to be tamed, teacher of gods and humans, enlightened, blessed.'[4]
              "And he will never infer of me according to Dhamma: 'That Blessed One enjoys the various kinds of supernormal power: having been one, he becomes many; having been many, he becomes one; he appears and vanishes; he goes unhindered through a wall, through an enclosure, through a mountain, as though through space; he dives in and out of the earth as though it were water; he walks on water without sinking as though it were earth; seated cross-legged, he travels in space like a bird; with his hand he touches and strokes the moon and sun so powerful and mighty; he wields bodily mastery even as far as the Brahma-world.'     
                  "And he will never infer of me according to Dhamma: 'With the divine ear element, which is purified and surpasses the human, that Blessed One hears both kinds of sounds, the heavenly and the human, those that are far as well as near.'  
                  "And he will never infer of me according to Dhamma: 'That Blessed One encompasses with his own mind the minds of other beings, other persons. He understands a mind affected by lust as affected by lust and a mind unaffected by lust as unaffected by lust; he understands a mind affected by hate as affected by hate and a mind unaffected by hate as unaffected by hate; he understands a mind affected by delusion as affected by delusion and a mind unaffected by delusion as unaffected by delusion; he understands a contracted mind as contracted and a distracted mind as distracted; he understands an exalted mind as exalted and an unexalted mind as unexalted; he understands a surpassed mind as surpassed and an unsurpassed mind as unsurpassed; he understands a concentrated mind as concentrated and an unconcentrated mind as unconcentrated; he understands a liberated mind as liberated and an unliberated mind as unliberated.' 
                                 
               ( "Maha-sihanada Sutta: The Great Discourse on the Lion's Roar" (MN 12), translated from the Pali by Ñanamoli Thera & Bhikkhu Bodhi. Access to Insight (BCBS Edition), 30 November 2013, http://www.accesstoinsight.org/tipitaka/mn/mn.012.ntbb.html . )

Comment:
𝗥𝘂𝘀𝘀𝗶𝗮-𝗨𝗸𝗿𝗮𝗶𝗻𝗲 𝗪𝗮𝗿: 𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗣𝗮𝗻𝗱𝗼𝗿𝗮 𝗕𝗼𝘅 𝗶𝘀 𝗢𝗽𝗲𝗻
The ramifications of this war run much deeper than the impact it will cause to those directly involved in the conflict. It will reshape the world, as it is likely that other latent frictions between countries and territories will be activated as a consequence of the Russia-Ukraine situation. This war just opened an era of wars, small and large, between different peoples.
UK Prime Minister Boris Johnson recently said that this war could easily become "the biggest war in Europe since 1945", and I agree. If countries with similar backgrounds cannot reach agreement between them, then how much more likely it is that several countries that have big differences and ancient conflicts may easily slip into war for no apparent justifiable reason.
On a personal level, it saddens me to see how fate turns around and once again we find ourselves at war. I am sorry and restless since I have many students in Russia and Ukraine who are under threat and feel how the deteriorating situation is affecting them and the whole world. In Israel, too, I have many students who follow with concern what is happening in Eastern Europe, anxious about the fate of their family members and friends.
My hope is that the manifestations of hatred between the Russians and the Ukrainians will stop soon, two peoples who have lived side by side throughout history. If it were still possible, I would give everything I could to silence, calm down, avoid the escalation, but this is impossible for now. 
There is not much that we can do at this stage. We can only long for peace and a ceasefire, talk about all parties showing restraint. The parties in conflict could follow the example of the Native American tribes who buried their hostility in a ceremony during which previously warring tribes agreed to settle their differences and live in harmony, and sealed their agreement by the chief of each tribe burying a war hatchet in the ground. 
Such a scenario does not look realistic under the current circumstances. Thus, above the forces of hostility, above the egoism and control as the driving forces of all the conflicts in the world, we can only raise a global prayer for peace, asking that we all get along with everyone. Because only in the power of connection and in the connection between our hearts, can a great positive force arise, a force that is able to unite all parties, to reconcile the haters, to awaken the truth in us all that we all belong to one soul. As it is written, “He who makes peace in His heights, may He make peace upon us…” (The Book of Job)

Comment:
Buckingham, We Have A Problem

‘Leave Princess Catherine alone!’ That needs to be directed to ‘The Firm’. If I was Catherine, Princess of Wales, I would have told whoever told me I needed to put a photo out, whilst in recovery, to politely  bugger off. Whether Catherine has full control over her narrative to do that, we will not know. 
We all know what happened to Diana, Princess of Wales when she tried to be firm with The Firm – her health suffered terribly. 
Catherine did not need to answer to the public or press with a photo for Mothers Day. I certainly didn’t expect a peep out of her until she returned back. Why did The Firm feel that a photo was needed? Why stress her out with this? And then leave her to explain?
Why give specific details about what type of surgery she was having? That sent women on the Internet all over the place, with their theories on what health condition she had!

Catherine hasn’t had a great start with The Firm  – She was being treated under tragic circumstances, in which a nurse, Jacintha Suldanha, took her own life. How could this have happened? How 2 were radio DJs able to get the number to the hospital? And to have a 2 minute call with Catherine’s nurse?!? Why hadn’t The Firm and the Hospital put strict protocols in place to ensure Catherine’s privacy? Jacintha was responsible for 3 wards – that should have been her ONLY responsibility.  No receptionist on duty at night? With a future Queen in the early stages of pregnancy? Ridiculous!
Catherine was then subsequently trotted out not long after she gave birth to face the cameras. It was commented at the time that Catherine gave a ‘sickly’ smile. Not surprised given the circumstances. No way should she have expected to face the press so soon, she didn’t look up to it. 

And The Firm have done it again!
1)	Trotting her out with William on a ‘shopping trip’ to PROVE she will be up and ready for duties. Why do this? Why not ‘kill’ the picture? Why just instead leave her be with her children?
2)	Not locking down Catherine’s medical records, how were/are 3 people being investigated? 
3)	Days later Catherine in trotted out again this time to record a video about her health condition. WTF is going on at The Firm? WHY does Catherine have to do a video? And no, I will not watch it. She should not have done this! The Firm should have been protecting her recovery and privacy!!! Unacceptable! 

Katie Razzall writes that, ‘there’s anger at what some perceive as bullying of the princess, with the suggestion that she was forced into making the video, rather than the more usual route of a written statement, by the relentless and far-fetched swirling conspiracy theories’ yet begins her piece with ‘ most of us in that position don’t feel compelled’… ‘… and having to make it public’. Catherine did not have to make it public, and she should not have felt compelled and that’s the concern. 
I found the timing of this video suspect. If The Firm thinks that they have the public as putty in their hands over the past weekend in the hope by the end of this week it will just all go away; if they think they can stage the return of Catherine without any questions being asked, then they are mistaken.

Victoria Newton cites Catherine not wanting her children at school to be asked ‘more than they already were’. So, 3 children aged 10 years and younger were already being asked about their mothers’ health condition? What were The Firm, teachers, and head teacher doing at the school to manage the situation? Where was the safe space for these children to tell what was happening to them? 
Doesn’t the school have an anti- bullying/harassment policy? It needs looking at again after this! If these were my children, I would remove them from this school and place them in another one. Don’t protect my children; don’t get to teach my children. Who is this ‘close friend’ who is reporting? I wouldn’t want my closest friends blabbing their mouths to a newspaper. The Firm needs to have, let’s just say, a ‘quiet word’ with this close friend. 


As for commenter’s who said ‘She told us she’d be back by end of Easter!’ It wasn’t Catherine who told us, it was The Firm. The Firm have since backtracked with Catherine returning ‘to official duties when she is cleared to do so by her medical team’. Oh I see when The Firm decide. Shouldn’t Catherine also be involved in her care plan in deciding/clearing when she feels ready to return? 
The Firm have a history of trotting women out when it is obvious to the human eye that they are physically unwell. So if there were no online discussion or hash tags, would Catherine been put back to duties by end of Easter? 

It’s not as Victoria Newton says’ crazy online speculation gone out of control’. It’s crazy that The Firm did not control the situation at the beginning, instead leaving Catherine solely to deal with it!
We have since been told that William, Catherine and their children are ‘not expected' to attend the Easter Sunday Service at St George’s Chapel at Windsor Castle. However The Firm ironically ‘expected’ William to appear at an investiture ceremony at Windsor Castle, February 27th, and appear at an event celebrating The Earthshot Prize Launchpad, March 11th.  But William can’t be expected with his 3 children to attend the Easter Sunday Service? Because Catherine is unable to attend, the rest of the family are not able to? Does The Firm need a woman to do everything? 
If I was Catherine, I would expect William to take the children to the Easter Service on Sunday. All 3 children each buy a candle for mummy which they could light once inside the church – Simple!
I can see Diana, Princess of Wales saying ‘Come on William! Pull your socks up – you’ve got this!’ Any change in Catherine’s health and William is notified immediately.

Katie Razzall again writes that this reminded her of Diana, Princess of Wales passing, and that the Queen ‘…had been trying to protect her family, prioritising her grandsons after the loss of their mother’. By William and Harry being trotted out so soon after the death of their mother, to look at bouquets of flowers and, and to engage with the public? I will say it now as I said it then, it was way too soon, much too soon for the boys. 
The pubic did not demand to see the boys or expect that they should make an appearance. The request at the time was for the then Queen Elizabeth II to make a statement. The understanding being by the public that the boys were being fully supported and prepared to attend their mother’s funeral. The Firm cannot blame solely outside of themselves and demand privacy for a 42 year old mother, when they themselves could not offer it to 2 boys who lost their 36 year old mother. 


For The Firm to want the bullying on social media to stop against Catherine are the same Firm who for decades failed to manage the behaviour of Andrew and his verbal trolling of staff. Is it any surprise Andrew is in the mess he is in now? 

To those who say ‘No.One.Cares.About.A.Photo’  - well Catherine obviously did! Please feel free to watch the mocking video of the photo with Catherine and her children manipulated to be ‘singing’ and tell me if that isn’t a problem. I saw a snippet of it on a news channel and found it disturbing. Catherine and her children did not deserve that. That needs to be ‘killed’. The Firm? 
‘What more do you need to lay off her?’ Well what more did YOU need Nelson Silva?  I for one did not expect or want any pictures of Catherine to be published until she had returned back to duties.
After this debacle, The Firm needs to accept they made gross errors in the handling of Catherine’s health and extend Catherine’s leave to at least end of June 2024. (I personally feel she needs another 6 months off) If she reports back to duty any earlier, I doubt she will be recovered 100% and may lead to a further re-admission in the year for something related either exhaustion and/or depression. Can The Firm ensure that this does not happen? 

As commented ‘The math isn’t mathing’ ; ‘The palace actually created the narrative, they only have themselves to blame’ ; ‘Pain absolutely has a hierarchy, the more privilege and resources you have, the easier hardship is to bare’ 

The Firm,

King Charles II needs to hand the throne to his sister Anne, Princess Royal. I am not convinced that in the last 13 years, The Firm had adequately advised and supported William and Catherine to take to the throne. They need more time and input.  I know that this would horrify the press and royalists who want a youthful looking King and Queen for their photo albums, but TOUGH. It’s about who can realistically do the job, and the job needs doing ASAP, if the monarchy is to survive up until the first half of the 21st century. 

Andrew needs to leave... now. Don’t get me wrong, I have had to get my house in order regarding ‘family’ and ‘friends’, just like everyone else. This is a lesson for us all.

A representative of The Firm must now be prepared to be interviewed by BBC World Service –Hard Talk regarding observations and concerns I and many others have posted about the monarchy, the handling of Catherine’s privacy over the past 10 years. This interview needs to be extended to 46 minutes. 

The Firm should, at the very least, offer a stay at Balmoral for William, Catherine and their children for the Easter holidays away from the media, if they truly care for their, as said by Paddy Harverson former Royal Spokesman, ‘time to heal’.

I’m done for now.

Comment: In the grand hierarchy of election-year issues, abortion isn't, nor should it be the number 1 issue ahead of the economy and national security. Unfortunately, abortion outranks the other two in the minds of too many voters. The economy determines whether or not families will be able to put food on the table. National security determines whether we will be able to live our lives in safety. Abortion directly affects all women who are of child-bearing age, whether or not they are old enough to vote, but it doesn't determine a family's financial destiny nor can it guarantee our safety from existential threats. The reality is that people are going to vote as though abortion does matter more. If all you can say is, it's a state matter, that doesn't bring any relief to those who felt wronged by the SCOTUS decision. We need to bring back a sense of propriety and proportion. It's the single, biggest wedge issue of our lifetimes and the most distraction from what is most important.

Comment: Listen, I totally agree that you shouldn't park in handicapped spots if you're able to walk up to 150 feet without difficulty.  I had a person with state-issued handicapped plates attempt to assault me after walking 200 feet.  However, many businesses don't have any LEGAL disabled parking spots.  A legal spot requires the blue sign, painting a logo on the pavement means nothing.  Until we can get a slight compensation for submitting photos of actual violations, a TV commercial isn't going to help one bit!  Our law enforcement is under fire already, and facing nationwide ridicule.  They don't have the manpower to enforce such a minor thing.  Shaming those types of people doesn't help either.  If they see 3 open disabled spots in a lot that's at 98 percent capacity do you think they're going to remember this ad when they choose a parking spot?  On the other hand, My father-a disabled Veteran-was issued a parking ticket for parking in such a spot.  He simply forgot to display his state-issued placard.  He paid it.  (it was a metered parking spot which have different identification requirements, much less noticeable than a non-metered parking spot)  The system is broken and we SHOULD BE ADDRESSING IT WITH OUR REPRESENTATION!

Comment:
Let’s just admit the truth. Handicap parking spaces are a stupid lie. People are truly handicapped may find them useful just as they find handicapped restroom stalls very useful, but they are abused. Companies get paid to put them up with tax benefits, so they have far more of them than are needed leaving a great deal of parking space unused much of the time. Also, there are people who get parking stickers under false pretenses. Able people park in them all the time because they have a phony sticker or temporary plaque.

The same goes for restroom stalls. Just because it’s designed for wheelchairs doesn’t mean it’s reserved for them. They are almost never used by people in wheelchairs. But I have had a guy in a wheelchair come into the bathroom and scream at me for using and I told him off. How many times an hour does someone in a store use a stall? Once or twice? How many times do people in wheelchairs need the stall in a month? Once or twice? It just is completely abused. Comment:
【全球退党服务中心2024年02月18日讯】
（退党中心记者洪博报导）
北京有位警察化名“孤警”在退党网站发表声明表示，自己在墙内，曾是北京警察（已交辞职申请），“现在看清了中共的邪恶本质，发自内心想跟这个恐怖组织决裂，退出中国共产党，摘掉这个肮脏无耻的帽子。希望您能帮助我完成这个心愿，谢谢！”

河北省陈含辉是个年轻气盛的青年，曾经满怀憧憬地当了警察。可是没有像想象中一样去抓坏人保护一方平安，却被领导安排搞网络防火墙。他在工作中看到了很多以前不曾看过的网站，看到了很多真相，从而了解了中共的邪恶本质。

他声明中说，“原来我从小到大都是生长在受中共邪党欺骗的环境里，完全受中共邪党文化的教育。已经迷失掉了判别是非的标准。在看过《九评共产党》以后更加从思想上、从根源上认识了中共的邪恶本质。”

“本人早就不满中共对法轮功修炼者的残暴迫害，毕竟那些都是普通老百姓，而且都是好人，却受到无端的祸害。我在这里正式宣布声明三退。从此刻起，本人正式退出少先队、共青团和共产党，从此以后和中共断绝一切关系。 ”

淅江台州某派出所一陈姓警察，今年28岁，他也说，“明白了真象。我要退出曾经入过的共靑团及少先队组织，特此声明！”

南京的邵华曾经是一名警察，现在已经退休。他在退党声明中说，“每当提到我的职业，我一点也感受不到自豪。因为在中共国警察就是中共的锦衣卫，不是用来服务人民的，而是用来维稳、逮捕异议人士的！从反送中期间黑警打香港人，向香港人开枪，到白纸革命期间黑警帮中共抓捕示威者就能看出来。中共只会说美国警察暴力执法，却从不撒泡尿照照自己。故今日正式宣布退党！”

还有位警察说，刚开始镇压法轮功时，自己年轻无知受了蒙骗，为了争取立功入党，积极参与迫害，根本不听法轮功学员讲的真相。“干的真的不是人的事，我的名字都上了明慧网的恶人榜。”

“缺德事做多了，就遭报应。”他说，“这个道理我体会最深！我现在全身都是病，活该！”“我现在办‘病退’或是‘退休’手续，等办下来了，我就用真名去网上办三退，公开道歉，求得你们宽恕！”

法轮功学员告诉他，“只要你真诚认罪、痛改前非、不再作恶、远离邪恶，弥补损失，相信大法会网开一面，给你机会的。”

中共恶警迫害好人
据明慧网报导，2023年山东至少1713名法轮功学员遭中共迫害，其中16人被迫害离世、149人被非法判刑、776人被绑架、425人被非法抄家（含搜身）、414人被关押、582人被骚扰、31人被迫流离失所、61人被非法关洗脑班、136人被非法取保候审、122人遭经济迫害（包括被法院罚款、警察勒索抢劫、被非法扣除养老金、绩效工资等）。

法轮功学员信仰真、善、忍，做好人，却遭到中共的严酷迫害，而执行迫害的主要是号称“为人民服务”，保一方平安的“人民”警察。

如山东烟台市牟平区国家税务局干部任青柏，因坚守“真、善、忍”信仰，多次遭中共人员绑架、勒索、关押，曾被非法劳教两年。2022年8月5日又遭警察绑架、非法关押，于2023年7月24日含冤离世，终年57岁。

山东寿光市法轮功学员魏兰英老人，2017年12月5日被警察绑架到济南女子监狱迫害两年。出狱回家后，遭派出所、镇政府人员骚扰，长期处于紧张状态，于2023年6月5日离世

山东青岛市56岁的法轮功学员徐海红女士，被警察砸门破锁绑架、非法关押在即墨普东看守所，被非法判刑一年四个月，2023年12月9日含冤离世。

共产党是硕鼠，警匪一家
黑龙江省佳木斯市政府机关干部牛生莲在三退声明中揭露中共治下是警匪一家，警察如盗。有一次，牛生莲在商业城听一老板说小偷盗窃的事。牛生莲问老板为什么不报案？老板说警匪一家，报案也没用。那几个小偷他们都认识，警察从来没管过。其实警匪是一家。

牛生莲还讲了警察如盗的情况。一农村孩子读高中住在朋友家。高考时学校要住址证明。朋友找警察说明情况要开证明，警察不给开。朋友没办法，给警察500元钱。警察收了钱，就给开了住址证明。

邻居家夜间被盗，丢了苹果新手机。十几天后，此案告破，手机追回。警察一直找借口，不把手机返还失主。邻居说，这手机从狼口进了虎口。

同时，牛生莲还列举了共产党权力腐败的例子，足见共产党腐败透顶。前几年，市检察院买新楼钱不够，到处勒索。找市水务局借了400万。半年以后，水务局去要钱不但没给，第二天就把水务局的会计带走审查。水务局局长赶紧去赔礼道歉，表示400万不要了，检察院才把会计放了。

市检察院还向市电业局借400万，电业局没借。第二天就把电业局的金柜查封，并带走出纳审查。电业局局长送去400万并赔礼道歉才了事。

找信用社主任要求赞助30万，不赞助的就审查。四十多家信用社的主任，无一幸免，全都赞助了30万。

牛生莲说，“我们市政府机关干部私下都骂共产党。可谓民怨鼎沸。“她用一首诗来形容：

共产党，群流氓，

祸国殃民没商量。

邪恶尽，丧天良，

从上到下贪腐忙。

窝里斗，整人狂， 

党风败坏民心散，

大好河山满创伤。

祸起共产党！

退了共产党。 

黑龙江省佳木斯市胡欣莲因要做买卖买了一辆汽车。车落户时交警队要住址证明。她拿户口、房产证都不行，就要派出所的证明。她到派出所和值班警察说明情况，值班警察说户口和房证就是最好的证明，还要什么证明，这是刁难你；要么你去告他；要么你去找中介。

后来，她找到片警，片警说连不上网。她跑了三天，也没办下汽车落户手续。被逼无奈，她花了三百元钱找中介，中介当天就办完了。她这才意思到警察和中介有交易。

她在三退声明中说，“警察明目张胆地刁难勒索百姓。共产恶党有权的都像硕鼠，蚕食百姓利益。我退出恶党的团、队组织。并用《硕鼠》表达人民的心声。”
